    <h3>Adaptation notes</h3>
    <p>The source chapter treats the cell as an economic consumer, works the overflow-metabolism example as Giffen behavior, and derives a linear response relation and a law of diminishing returns. We make the central trade-off (rate-per-protein beating yield) runnable, and point to the source for the Giffen construction and the response relations, which deserve their full treatment.</p>

